shapes.css:
	   Dynamic CSS shapes, change only container size
	   
	   Gathered from different sources:
	   http://css3shapes.com/
	   http://css-tricks.com/examples/ShapesOfCSS/
	   http://www.russellheimlich.com/blog/pure-css-shapes-triangles-delicious-logo-and-hearts/
	   
License: Public Domain


HOWTO:
   
     Put the shape inside a size container class,
     then you'll have to set height and width only once.
     
     Create more/modify container classes as needed.

     Note: The size of some of the shapes is derived from the font-size (em)
